### Amiga Retro Games Sunday and "Sensible Soccer" Tournament! 

The Amiga turned 40 this year, and c-base 30. Reason enough to relive the days of demo parties, floppy disk games, and analog joysticks. We're diving into the golden era of 16-bit games! 

Join us for the fascination of blockbusters like Lemmings, Settlers, Secret of Monkey Island, Worms, Turrican, and more. These retro games still impress even today with their incredible playability. 

Here's what you can expect: 

- "Best of Amiga Demoscene" on the big screen 
- "Sensible Soccer" and "Dynablaster" tournaments with great prizes like a retro gaming console and joysticks 
- Computers you can use to play games or get creative with DigiPaint and Music-X.

Since our Amiga hardware is old and fragile, the tournaments will be run using emulation on Linux computers. 

Bringing your own hardware, such as laptops or even original devices, is encouraged. ([Registration desired](mailto:rubbel@c-base.org?subject=Registration%20for%20Retro%20Games%20Sunday))

If you wish, we can help you install and set up an emulator. (FS-UAE) 

Link with instructions follows.
